       para3aa: "In order to create an Account, you must provide your e-mail and choose a strong password, among other things. The e-mail address and chosen password, together, form the ",
       logincredentials: "Login Credentials.",
       para3b: "You are fully responsible for non-disclosure of your Login Credentials and the use of your Account. You may not allow use of your Account by any third party nor others that do not have the authority to represent you. You guarantee that any third party that uses your Account is authorized to represent you. If you suspect that your Account has been breached, you will report this immediately to support@opinionbar.com.",
       para3c: "You agree to only provide correct and complete information when creating an Account on the Platform. You are responsible for the accuracy of the data in your Account.",
       para3d: "You may request to cancel/terminate your Account by contacting OpinionBar. OpinionBar may need to retain certain information as required by law or as necessary for its business purposes. For more information about the processing of personal data, please see the ",
       para3e: "At our discretion, we are entitled to suspend, block, or delete the Account of any Panellist at all times. You are not entitled to any compensation from us in connection with such suspension, blocking or deletion of the Account and you hereby waive any right to any compensation of damages.",
       para4heading: "4 OUR PANELLIST AGREEMENT WITH YOU AND REWARDS",
       para4a: "You create an Account on our Platform to become a ",
       panellist: "Panellist",
       para4aa: " After you create an Account, you can provide us with more personal data on the basis of which we build your profile (",
       registrationdata: "Registration Data and (Additional) Profile Data",
       para4ab: "). Based on these personal data, we will invite you to Surveys for which you are a relevant Panellist. The more (Additional) Profile Data you provide to us, the more you will be invited to relevant Surveys. For each Survey you complete as our Panellist you will be awarded with a",
       rewards: "Reward(s)",
       para4ac: " This way of working is our ",
       panellistagreement: "Panellist Agreement",
       para4ad: " with you.",
       para4b: "Rewards have a value expressed in your local currency. The value of a Reward expressed in your local currency (the ",
       rewardamount: "Reward Amount",
       para4ba: ") for each individual Survey will be explained in the email invitation you receive or on the Website. The Reward Amount for some Surveys may vary based upon other factors, such as your choices regarding the sharing and use of your personal information, in which case we may communicate a range for the Reward Amount.",
       para4c: "You must complete the Survey in full and agree to share your data in accordance with the Privacy Notice in order to receive the full Reward Amount credited to your Account.",
       para4d: "Once you have earned a certain number of Rewards determined by us and communicated to you via your Account and/or the e-mail address linked to your account, you may access the ",
       rewardsarea: "Rewards Area",
       para4da: " of the Website. Select the desired redemption option from those listed on the Website and follow the instructions given to process your Reward. Rewards are never paid out in cash.",
       para4e: "The content of the Rewards Area and the minimum Reward redemption amount are subject to change by OpinionBar at any time without prior notice.",
       para4f: "OpinionBar assumes no liability, obligation, or responsibility for, and makes no warranty with respect to, any Rewards provided by Reward partners, or any part thereof.",
       para4g: "Rewards earned from participating in Surveys are valid for 12 calendar months as from the date that the Reward was credited to your account ",
       para4ga: " If a Reward remains unused on the 366th day after the Award Date, the Reward will expire and be removed from your Account balance. Upon usage, OpinionBar will redeem Rewards from your Account based on the Award Date: your “oldest” Rewards will be deducted first, leaving your most recently earned Rewards in your account.",
       awarddate: "Award Date",
       para5heading: "5 USE OF THE PLATFORM",
       para5a: "You must ensure that the Platform is used in conformity with OpinionBar’s instructions and for the purpose that OpinionBar intended them for. More specifically (without limitation), you are not allowed to use the Platform:",
       para5b: "in any way that affects the integrity or continuity of OpinionBar’s systems; or",
