       para5d: "It is your responsibility to use the Platform in compliance with applicable law and with any third-party rights. More specifically (without limitation), you are not allowed to use the Platform:",
       para5e: "in a way that infringes on a third party's intellectual property rights;",
       para5f: "in a way that violates a person's privacy;",
       para5g: "in a way that is obscene, lewd, lascivious, filthy, violent, harassing, fraudulent libellous or slanderous or otherwise objectionable (as determined by us), or that ridicules, mocks, disparages, intimidates, or abuses anyone;",
       para5h: "to send unsolicited messages to OpinionBar or any third-party recipient.",
       para6heading: "6 AVAILABILITY OF THE PLATFORM AND WARRANTY DISCLAIMER",
       para6a: "OpinionBar will use reasonable efforts to make the Platform available at all times. OpinionBar does not accept any responsibility whatsoever for unavailability of the Platform, or any difficulty or inability to download or access content, or any other communication system failure which may result in the Platform being unavailable.",
       para6b: "OpinionBar is not responsible for any support or maintenance regarding the Platform. OpinionBar may – at its own discretion – update, modify, or adapt the Platform and its functionalities from time to time to enhance your experience. This may result in any downtime for which OpinionBar is not responsible.",
       para6c: "To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, OpinionBar hereby disclaims all implied warranties regarding the availability of the Platform. The Platform is provided “as is” and “as available” without warranty of any kind.",
       para6d: "OpinionBar does not make any warrantees or guarantees with respect to:",
       para6e: "the number of Surveys to which you as our Panellist will be invited;",
       para6f: "value of the subsequent Rewards earned; and",
       para6g: "the fact that our Services correspond with the expectations you as our Panellist may have in light of earning Rewards.",
       para7heading: "7 THIRD PARTY SITES AND SERVICES",
       para7a: "The Platform or Website may contain content that links to other websites, services or resources on the internet, and other websites, services or resources may contain links to the Platform or Website. As a Panellist, you access third party websites at your own risk. These other websites are not under OpinionBar’s control, and you acknowledge that OpinionBar is not responsible or liable for the content, functions, accuracy, legality, appropriateness or any other aspect of such websites or resources. The inclusion of any such link does not imply endorsement by OpinionBar or any association with its operators. You further acknowledge and agree that OpinionBar shall not be responsible or liable, directly or indirectly, for any damage or loss caused or alleged to be caused by or in connection with the use of or reliance on any such content, goods or services available on or through any such third-party website or resource.",
       para7b: "In order to participate in a Survey, you may be directed to websites, services, or resources of our Clients, e.g. via the Platform or via a hyperlink in an e-mail sent by us. You agree that you will act in accordance with these Terms on such websites, services, or resources as if you were acting on the Platform. You may be asked to accept third-party terms and conditions before being eligible to participate in a Survey. We have no responsibility and/or liability in this regard and you waive all rights to claim otherwise. You agree that you will verify thoroughly whether the communication really originates from us or is endorsed by us. If you have any doubts as to the legitimacy of requests to participate in a Survey on a third-party website, please let us know before using hyperlinks and/or providing personal information.",
       para8heading: "8 TERM AND TERMINATION",
       para8a: "The Agreement between you and OpinionBar is for an indefinite period and starts at the moment you create an Account.",
       para8b: "The Agreement can be terminated by you by deleting your Account with or without cause at any time without termination period.",
       para8c: "OpinionBar can terminate the Agreement if you have not logged on for 24 months. In such case, OpinionBar will first send a reminder to your e-mail address that is linked to your Account.",
       para8d: "If you terminate your Account, (part of) the information may be irrevocably deleted immediately (or at any time in the future). Any unclaimed Rewards will be lost and cannot be reclaimed or otherwise reinstated at a later stage. OpinionBar recommends making a copy of what you consider important to keep before terminating your Account.",
