       para13heading: "13 CONFIDENTIALITY",
       para13a: "The Panellist agrees to maintain secret and confidential all information (any information in any form disclosed) of which the Panellist has understood or should reasonably understand that it is to be regarded as confidential (",
       para13ab: "), unless prior written approval of OpinionBar is received.",
       confidential: "Confidential Information",
       para13b: "Confidential Information may include but is not limited to: new product ideas or concepts, packaging concepts, advertising, and movie or television concepts or trailers, and the text, visual images and sounds related thereto.",
       para13c: "The Panellist agrees that when accessing the Confidential Information, he or she will not copy, print, store, forward or otherwise collect the Confidential Information, and will not disclose the Confidential Information to anyone (unless as directed by the owner of the Confidential Information) and will not use the confidential information for the express purpose for which it was disclosed to the Panellist.",
       para13d: "If the Panellist violates any of this clause 13, this will be considered a breach of these Terms and may result in the termination of his or her Account and the forfeiture of all Rewards in that Account. It also may be considered a breach of civil and criminal law. OpinionBar and its Clients reserve the right to enforce any such laws against the Panellist.",
       para13e: "OpinionBar and the Panellist are not liable for compensation of damages or indemnification, if they are required by law to disclose the confidential information and comply with this statutory duty.",
       para14heading: "14 MISCELLANEOUS",
       para14a: "No omission or delay on the part of OpinionBar in exercising any right, power or remedy under these Terms shall prejudice or impair such right, power or remedy or be construed as a waiver thereof. Any single or partial exercise of such right, power or remedy shall not preclude any other or future exercise thereof or the exercise of any other right, power, or remedy.",
       para14b: "OpinionBar reserves the right to unilaterally modify or replace these Terms at any time if OpinionBar finds this reasonably necessary and useful. When OpinionBar changes these Terms in a significant way, we will notify you via email and/or through the Platform and/or in your Account. If you qualify as a consumer, you will be offered the possibility to opt-out on material amendments to the terms by terminating your agreement (including your Account) with us within 30 calendar days as from notification of such amendment.",
       para14c: "Except as explicitly stated otherwise, any notices given to OpinionBar shall be given by email to the address listed in the contact information below. Any notices given to you shall be given to the email address provided during the registration process, or such other address as you may specify in your Account. Notice shall be deemed to be given twenty-four (24) hours after the email is sent, unless the sending party is notified that the email address is invalid. OpinionBar may also choose to send notices by regular mail.",
       para14d: "If any provision of these Terms is found to be unenforceable or invalid, that provision will be limited or eliminated to the maximum extent necessary, so that the rest of these Terms will remain in full force and effect and stay enforceable. Any such unenforceable or invalid provision shall be replaced or be deemed to be replaced by a provision that is valid and enforceable, and which interpretation shall be as close as possible to the intent of the invalid provision.",
       para14e: "You cannot transfer your rights and obligations under these Terms to third parties. OpinionBar may assign and/or transfer all rights and obligations under these Terms to a third party, without your consent being required, provided that, if you are a consumer, (i) OpinionBar remains jointly liable for the performance of these Terms by the assignee/transferee, (ii) the assignment/transfer is effectuated in connection with a transfer of an enterprise which encompasses the liabilities and corresponding rights under these Terms, or (iii) you have been given 30 days as from the moment the assignment/transfer is communicated to you to terminate your Account.",
       para14f: "All provisions of these Terms which by their nature should survive termination shall survive termination, including, without limitation, ownership provisions, warranty disclaimers, indemnity, and limitations of liability.",
       para15heading: "15 APPLICABLE LAW AND COMPETENT COURT",
       para15a: "These Terms and any (non-)contractual disputes in relation to these Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Netherlands. Panellists who qualify as consumers and domiciled within the European Union will benefit from any mandatory provision of the law of the country in which they are resident.",
       para15b: "In the event of a dispute resulting from or arising in connection with these Terms between the Panellist and OpinionBar, the Panellist and OpinionBar will attempt to resolve this dispute in the first instance by mutual consultation and try to find a solution together.",
       para15c: "Unless mandatory law compels differently, all (non-)contractual disputes resulting from or arising in connection with these Terms shall be exclusively submitted to the competent court of Rotterdam, the Netherlands. This clause 15.3 only applies when the Panellist and OpinionBar could not settle the dispute in an amicable fashion as described in clause 15.2 above.",
